detaileddescription.para: Optimizes switch statement code generation by eliminating unnecessary jumps when the switch has no cases.
Optimizes switch statement jump table lookups by eliminating redundant conditional jumps.
Replaces movl/cmpl/je sequences with direct cmpl/je when possible, eliminating unnecessary register loads for constant comparisons.
Replaces movl/cmpl/jne sequences with direct cmpl/jne when possible, eliminating unnecessary register loads for constant comparisons.
Optimizes less-than comparisons by eliminating register loads and reversing comparison operands when beneficial.
Optimizes greater-than comparisons by eliminating register loads and reversing comparison operands when beneficial.
Optimizes less-than-or-equal comparisons by eliminating register loads and reversing comparison operands when beneficial.
Optimizes greater-than-or-equal comparisons by eliminating register loads and reversing comparison operands when beneficial.

briefdescription.para: Pattern for array access comparison optimization.

detaileddescription.para: Combines array access and comparison into a single instruction, eliminating the intermediate register load.

briefdescription.para: Pattern for array access register comparison optimization.

detaileddescription.para: Combines array access and register comparison into a single instruction, eliminating the intermediate register load.
Replaces multiplication by 2 with a left shift operation, which is more efficient on most processors.
Combines load-modify-store sequences into direct memory operations, eliminating unnecessary register traffic.

briefdescription.para: Pattern for equality test with setcc optimization.

detaileddescription.para: Optimizes equality comparisons that set condition codes, eliminating unnecessary register loads for constant comparisons.

briefdescription.para: Pattern for inequality test with setcc optimization.

detaileddescription.para: Optimizes inequality comparisons that set condition codes, eliminating unnecessary register loads for constant comparisons.

briefdescription.para: Pattern for less-than test with setcc optimization.

detaileddescription.para: Optimizes less-than comparisons that set condition codes, eliminating register loads and reversing operands when beneficial.

briefdescription.para: Pattern for greater-than test with setcc optimization.

detaileddescription.para: Optimizes greater-than comparisons that set condition codes, eliminating register loads and reversing operands when beneficial.
Combines memory load and comparison into direct memory comparison, eliminating intermediate register usage.
Combines memory load and register comparison into direct memory-register comparison, eliminating intermediate register load.
Replaces movl $1 + addl sequence with movl + incl, which is more efficient for incrementing by 1.
Replaces movl $-1 + addl sequence with movl + decl, which is more efficient for decrementing by 1.
Replaces addl $1 with the more efficient incl instruction.
Replaces addl $-1 with the more efficient decl instruction.
Replaces subl $1 with the more efficient decl instruction.
Replaces subl $-1 (subtract negative one) with incl (increment), which is equivalent but more efficient.
Eliminates addl $0,eax instructions which have no effect.
Eliminates redundant load operations when a value is stored and immediately loaded back from the same location.
Eliminates jump instructions to the immediately following label, which are unnecessary and waste execution time.

briefdescription.para: Pattern for left shift by 1 optimization.

detaileddescription.para: Replaces variable left shift by 1 with immediate left shift, avoiding unnecessary register setup for the shift count.

briefdescription.para: Pattern for right shift by 1 optimization.

detaileddescription.para: External pattern table from pt.c.
Replaces variable right shift by 1 with immediate right shift, avoiding unnecessary register setup for the shift count.

briefdescription.para: Peephole optimizer pattern definitions for BCPL compiler.

detaileddescription.para:
Robert Nordier
2012
This file contains pattern definitions used by the peephole optimizer to improve generated assembly code. The patterns define common sequences of instructions that can be replaced with more efficient equivalents.

Each pattern array contains:
Original instruction sequence to match
Replacement instruction sequence (after NULL terminator)

simplesect.para: op.c for the pattern matching and replacement engine
